A large bay window invites light and views to living room. A family with 6 children has lived here since 1990's and have accumulated lots of stuff. It makes it hard to appreciate how much room this house really offers! It could easily be 5 bedrooms by adding a closet to downstairs 14'X12' den. Home's adaptable floor plan suits a variety of uses and households. Also, note the detached double garage, good parking plus a storage shed. In bonus side/play yard there's room for a jungle gym or a volleyball game, gardens or ???! Please, check map to acquaint yourself with lot shape. Exclude curtains in 2 upstairs BR.   Convenient to main traffic arteries. Abundant shopping choices nearby.

Recently sold: $265,000. This remodeled rambler is ideally situated in a nice neighborhood with easy access to Brooklyn Blvd, Highway 100 and several area parks and retail destinations. The collection of modern conveniences this home offers is very hard to match in this area and price range. Open floor plan with tons of natural light. Brand new kitchen. New flooring throughout. A mud room. A walk-in pantry. Newer high-quality double-pane wood windows. Walk-in master bedroom closet.  Remodeled bathrooms. A HUGE back yard fully enclosed with a privacy fence. Three-car garage. The architectural-shingled roof is just 5 years old and the furnace was installed new February 2019. Lower level is plumbed to become a mother-in-law suite in a matter of about one day, and there is a washer/dryer hook-up in the main floor pantry for those who may prefer complete main-floor living.
